# 배당률이 0 or 음수인 행 제거
soccer <- soccer[!(soccer$home_odd <=0),]

# 필요없는 열 정리
soccer <- soccer[,-c(1:4)]              
soccer <- subset(soccer, select = -c(h_offensiv, h_defensiv, a_offensiv, a_defensiv, h_final, a_final))
soccer <- soccer %>% filter(h_played>=5)
soccer <- subset(soccer, select = -c(h_played, a_played))

# RESULT 열 factor로 변환
soccer$RESULT <- as.factor(soccer$RESULT)

축구에 Home advantage가 있을까?

x <-prop.table(table(soccer$RESULT))
x <- as.data.frame(x)
x$Freq <- round(round(x$Freq*100))
x<- rename(x, RESULT = Var1)
x
  RESULT Freq
1   AWAY   30
2   DRAW   27
3   HOME   43
ggplot(x, aes(x="", y=Freq, fill=RESULT)) + geom_bar(stat="identity", width=1) +
  coord_polar("y", start=0) + 
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(Freq), "%")), position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
  theme_void() +labs(title = "승무패 비율") + theme(plot.title = element_text(face="bold", size =(20)))

90% 이상 결과를 맟추는 배당률은?

soccer$min <- do.call(pmin, soccer[ , c(1:3)])

s1 <- soccer %>% subset(select = c(home_odd, draw_odd, away_odd, min, RESULT ))

s1$PREDICT <- ifelse(s1$min == s1$home_odd,"HOME",
                     ifelse(s1$min==s1$draw_odd, "DRAW","AWAY"))
s1$PREDICT <- as.factor(s1$PREDICT)

HOME 배당률(home_odd) 예측

# 다중선형회귀

# 배당률과  다른 변수들의 관계 / 예측
s3k <- soccer[,1:39]

# home_odd만 봄
s3k$draw_odd=NULL
s3k$away_odd=NULL

sample_count = round(nrow(s3k)* 0.9)
set.seed(123)
sample_row <- sample(nrow(s3k), sample_count)

s3k_train <- s3k[sample_row,]
s3k_test <- s3k[-sample_row,]

# 다중선형회귀
regressor_lm <- lm(formula = home_odd ~. ,
                   data = s3k_train)        
summary(regressor_lm)                         # 선형회귀 NA ?

# regression tree

                     data = s3_train)

# 인공신경망 - 정규화
s5<- s3

s5_n <- as.data.frame(lapply(s5[-1],normalize))

sample_count = round(nrow(s5)* 0.9)
set.seed(123)
sample_row <- sample(nrow(s5), sample_count)

s5_n_train <- s5_n[sample_row,]
s5_n_test <- s5_n[-sample_row,]

s5_n_train$home_odd <- s5[sample_row,]$home_odd
s5_n_test$home_odd <- s5[-sample_row,]$home_odd

nn2 <- neuralnet(formula = home_odd~. , data = s5_n_train )
plot(nn2)
pred_nn2 <- compute(nn2, s5_n_test[-37] )

Pred_Actual_nn2 <- as.data.frame(cbind(Prediction = pred_nn2$net.result, Actual = s5_n_test$home_odd))

cor(pred_nn2$net.result, s5_n_test$home_odd)      
          [,1]
[1,] 0.7829245
MAE(pred_nn2$net.result, s5_n_test$home_odd)     
[1] 0.5095263
gg.nn2 <- ggplot(Pred_Actual_nn2, aes(Actual, V1 )) +
  geom_point() + theme_bw() + geom_abline() +
  labs(title = "Neural Net normalize", x = "Actual home odd",
       y = "Predicted home odd")
gg.nn2
